<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2011/05/11/this-week-in-spring-may-10th-2011">This Week in Spring: May 10th, 2011</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon engineering"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/engineering">Engineering</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="null?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<span class="author">Adam Fitzgerald</span>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2011-05-11 05:19:00.0">May 11, 2011</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="619" href="/blog/2011/05/11/this-week-in-spring-may-10th-2011#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p></p>
<p> May’s well underway and all the preparations for the <a href="http://www.springsource.org/node/3128">S2G Forums in Amsterdam and London</a> are complete. These S2G Forums are the premiere place for people in Europe to get access to the best information related to the Spring community (at a minimum cost!). I hope we’ll see you in <a href="http://www.springsource.com/events/s2gforum-5-26-2011-amsterdam">Amsterdam (May 26, 2011 - € 114 )</a> and / or <a href="http://www.springsource.com/events/s2gforum-5-31-2011-london">London (May 31, 2011 - &amp;#163 99)</a>!<br></p>
<br>
<p><br> In the interim, those of you that want an even better picture of how the Spring framework plays on the nascent CloudFoundry open-source cloud PaaS project should be sure to attend a webinar - Spring from Zero to Cloud in 60 minutes for both <a href="http://www.springsource.org/node/3126">North America</a> and <a href="http://www.springsource.org/node/3126">Europe</a> in just 10 short days!</p>
</div>
</section>
